description: Late 14th century, from Middle English misdemen, equivalent to mis- +‎ deem. Cognate with Icelandic misdæma (“to misjudge”).

verbs.description: misdeem (third-person singular simple present misdeems, present participle misdeeming, simple past and past participle misdeemed)

examples: The doubt which ye misdeem, fair love, is vain, / That fondly fear to lose your liberty; / […]
